From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 01/10] panvk: Track flow-end offset in pan_shader_info

Record the byte offset of the terminating VA_FLOW_END instruction in
the compiled binary. The fast-linker uses this to patch VA_FLOW_END ->
VA_FLOW_NONE when concatenating prolog/main/epilog binaries.

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 02/10] panfrost: Implement pan_fast_link() for Valhall binary
 concatenation

Add a linker that concatenates independently compiled prolog, main, and
epilog shader binaries by patching VA_FLOW_END flow control bits at
join points. Non-final parts are stripped of their 128-byte alignment
padding (which would cause INSTR_INVALID_ENC faults if executed).

This enables draw-time specialization without recompiling the main
shader.

Modeled after src/asahi/lib/agx_linker.c.

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 03/10] panfrost: Add unit tests for pan_fast_link()

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 04/10] panfrost: Add FS clip distance prolog NIR builder

Build a standalone fragment shader prolog that loads gl_ClipDistance
values from CLIP_DIST0/CLIP_DIST1 with perspective-correct
interpolation, multiplies by gl_FragCoord.w to recover linear
interpolation, and discards fragments where any clip distance is
negative.

This is compiled independently against the VS's varying layout and
concatenated with the main FS via pan_fast_link() at draw time.

Modeled after src/asahi/lib/agx_nir_prolog_epilog.c.

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 05/10] panvk: Add linked shader cache

Device-level hash table caching linked (prolog + main) shader binaries
and their SPD descriptors. Keyed on main shader binary pointer identity
and FS prolog parameters.

Invalidate cache entries when a shader is destroyed to prevent stale
pointer matches from malloc address reuse.

Modeled after src/asahi/vulkan/hk_shader.c's per-shader fast-link cache,
but kept device-level (with an explicit invalidate hook) so a single
prolog/main pair can be reused across pipelines that bind the same main
FS.

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 06/10] panfrost: Factor out pos-store / output-store helpers
 into pan_nir.h

Move pan_nir_find_pos_store() and pan_nir_move_output_stores_after()
from static functions in pan_nir_lower_noperspective.c to shared inlines
in pan_nir.h so they can be reused by the clip distance lowering passes.

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 07/10] panfrost: Add clip distance VS/FS lowering passes

Mali only supports perspective-correct or flat varying interpolation.
To get linear interpolation for clip distances:

- VS pass (pan_nir_lower_clip_distance_vs): Multiply clip distance
  store_outputs by position W before viewport transform.
- FS pass (pan_nir_lower_clip_distance_fs): Multiply
  load_interpolated_input at clip distance slots by FragCoord.w.

The matching FragCoord.w multiply is also baked into the standalone FS
clip prolog so a prolog-concatenated main FS sees linear values without
running the lowering pass on the prolog itself.

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 08/10] panvk: Remap clip distances to VAR slots before
 lowering

Move gl_ClipDistance from CLIP_DIST0/1 to VARYING_SLOT_VAR0+N before
IO lowering, then run pan_nir_lower_clip_distance_{vs,fs}.

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 09/10] panvk: Wire clip prolog into draw path

When a draw uses shader clip distance, look up a combined prolog + main
FS binary in the device's linked shader cache. On a miss, build the
clip distance FS prolog, compile it against the VS's varying layout so
its LD_VAR_BUF byte offsets for CLIP_DIST0/1 match what the main FS
reads, concatenate with the main FS via pan_fast_link(), upload the
combined binary, and cache an SPD descriptor pointing at it.

Set skip_atest on the prolog so it does not emit a second ATEST
alongside the main FS's. Account for the prolog's discard in
shader_modifies_coverage, allow_forward_pixel_to_kill, and early-Z /
late-Z update fields.

From: Christian Gmeiner <cgmeiner@igalia.com>
Subject: [PATCH 10/10] panvk: Advertise shaderClipDistance support

Enable shaderClipDistance with up to 8 clip distances. The clip
distance lowering is handled by the FS prolog at draw time via
pan_fast_link().

